- What's up?

06:02.400 --> 06:04.300
- [mumbles]
- Ooh.

06:04.300 --> 06:06.367
- I gathered stuff because I
knew you didn't have very long.

06:06.367 --> 06:08.133
- I'm so hungry.
- Good.

06:08.133 --> 06:09.433
- What's going on?

06:09.433 --> 06:11.266
- Not too much.
- Happy to be back

06:11.266 --> 06:13.200
and on the island?
- Yeah.

06:13.200 --> 06:14.433
I certainly wouldn't
want to be up--

06:14.433 --> 06:17.033
you know, in
that cold climate, so...

06:17.033 --> 06:18.533
- Gosh, this is really bare.

06:18.533 --> 06:20.467
I've never seen your--
- I just got into town

06:20.467 --> 06:22.400
on Tuesday from
being gone for five months.

06:22.400 --> 06:24.133
- That's true.
That's true.

06:24.133 --> 06:26.066
- We threw everything out.
- You are forgiven.

06:26.066 --> 06:27.467
[chuckling]
- God.

06:27.467 --> 06:30.033
- So this is
my old neighborhood.

06:30.033 --> 06:32.266
- Is it?
- Oh, we're already here.

06:32.266 --> 06:35.333
- My parents got divorced when
I was three.

06:35.333 --> 06:38.266
And then my mom met this man
named Jerry,

06:38.266 --> 06:40.300
and this was his house,
and so he kind of,

06:40.300 --> 06:42.266
like, took us in.
- Oh, okay.

06:42.266 --> 06:44.700
- I only remember happy times
in this neighborhood.

06:44.700 --> 06:48.300
We really didn't even know,
like, how bad we had it.

06:50.333 --> 06:53.233
- I wanna get a, uh,
French Bulldog, Mom.

06:53.233 --> 06:55.100
- Shepard, you don't
have any business

06:55.100 --> 06:56.633
getting a dog--
- I know. I know.

06:56.633 --> 06:58.300
But eventually, one day.
- Eventually.

06:58.300 --> 06:59.700
Yeah, that'd be good.

06:59.700 --> 07:02.066
- So I got knee surgery
on Friday.

07:02.066 --> 07:03.333
- That's tomorrow.

07:03.333 --> 07:05.433
- Kathryn is gonna
take me there

07:05.433 --> 07:07.100
and pick me up.

07:07.100 --> 07:10.066
- Oh, really?
- Yeah, Mom, she's...

07:10.066 --> 07:12.633
I just see
a lot of good in her.

07:12.633 --> 07:14.700
There's a few people
in this world

07:14.700 --> 07:17.166
who you never know
what you're gonna get.

07:17.166 --> 07:19.433
Kathryn was one of them
for a long time.

07:19.433 --> 07:21.233
I like seeing
the good in people.

07:21.233 --> 07:23.433
I'm sort of an optimist
in that way.

07:23.433 --> 07:25.100
- You should be.

07:25.100 --> 07:28.033
- But she's starting
to become more dependable.

07:28.033 --> 07:29.433
It's just the little things.

07:29.433 --> 07:31.367
The little things
always add up.

07:31.367 --> 07:34.633
And she's doing
a lot of those things.

07:34.633 --> 07:36.667
- What have you done
to your nose?

07:36.667 --> 07:39.467
